## ğŸ“¦ Compression & Archiving

### ğŸ”¸ `tar` â€“ Archive multiple files/directories

```bash
# Archive a directory (no compression)
tar -cvf archive.tar /path/to/dir

# Archive + gzip compress
tar -czvf archive.tar.gz /path/to/dir

# Archive + bzip2 compress
tar -cjvf archive.tar.bz2 /path/to/dir

# Extract a .tar.gz file
tar -xzvf archive.tar.gz

ğŸ”¸ gzip â€“ Compress a single file
# Compress a single file
gzip filename.txt

# Decompress
gunzip filename.txt.gz

 bzip2 â€“ Better compression than gzip
# Compress
bzip2 filename.txt

# Decompress
bunzip2 filename.txt.bz2

ğŸ” File Syncing with rsync + ssh

âœ… Task: Sync files from sasakovich to sastronik over SSH

# Basic rsync over SSH
rsync -avz -e ssh ~/Projects/ sasatronik@192.168.1.50:/home/sasatronik/Backups/

# Explanation:
# -a : archive mode (preserves perms, timestamps)
# -v : verbose
# -z : compress files during transfer
# -e ssh : use SSH as the transport layer

